Actually, it isn't.  We have Sarhea and Apep (to name a few) with signatures exposing the female nipple and those depictions are much more realistic than Krogoth's silly attempt.  I certainly wasn't offended by Krogoth's signature.  He isn't doing anything with the penis.  It looks like something my six-year old nephew may draw on a restaurant napkin when he is feeling bored and everyone would laugh.  If that same nephew would draw a depiction of two people having anal sex together (in what arguable could be considered a depiction of sexual assault), people wouldn't be laughing.    <br>
<br>
What is the standard then in deciding when a signature should be banned?  If the standard is whether the sig goes against the norms of decency, then I would wager that Gio's signature bothered more people than Krogoth's.  When Cielo was discussing the controversy over Gio's sig, she had mentioned that it was not porn and that anyone who had seen real porn would know that to be the case.  Fair enough.  I have seen porn myself and it is fair to say that Krogoth's depiction is further away than Gio's.<br>
